10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
11 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 915, is
12 amended to read as follows:
13 Section 915. Every person who willfully disturbs, interrupts,
14 or disquiets any assemblage of people met for religious worship, by
15 any of the acts or things hereinafter enumerated, is in Section 916
16 of this title shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a misdemeanor
17 punishable by a fine not to exceed Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00),
18 by imprisonment in the county jail for a term not to exceed one (1)
19 year, or by both such fine and imprisonment. A person who commits a
20 second or subsequent offense shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a
21 felony punishable by a fine not to exceed One Thousand Dollars
22 ($1,000.00), by imprisonment in the custody of the Department of
23 Corrections for a term not to exceed two (2) years, or by both such
24 fine and imprisonment.
